reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars I like it
reviews.reviewText: This imageCLASS MF267dw II replaces my 16 year old Canon imageCLASS. The old one could have been repaired, but it was cheaper to buy new. I really liked my old one, so I went ahead with this new model. It's fast and works fine. Setup is no problem. I had the thing up and connected to my Wi-Fi in minutes. It just works as advertised and should last a long time, (if my first one is any indication).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It prints just fine.
reviews.reviewText: It prints like it should. After all, it's a Canon.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works great but a few things disappointed me
reviews.reviewText: This laser printer works great. I believe the printer is great but the app/software problems needs to be Addressed, patched, updated and/or changed. I cannot scan, print, copy and just type a email address or reply with attachment from printer or forward it and send. It's a big production typing in on printer and after all that doesn't send.The remote App on iPhone way says I cannot use the feature.Also saving a document it only saves to drive which I never can find. It finds photos fine and old attachments but that doesn't help. I want to send a real time file legal document by email. It will save to on my phone but when I try to attach the file it will not come up to attach the file I want to email. I've tried many ways. I usually have to try to copy file and try to place it in a folder I can just open with email attachments. I email it to myself then TRY to copy it and send a new email to the person I am replying to. The software is really messed up. Buggy or something. And/or iphone12, gmail,or the Canon software. I just know when they all fix it to work in co very together it will be fast. Convenient. I just cannot stop and troubleshoot while working trying to send documents fast to attorneys, doctors, legal stuff they need. I end up having to find sone way just to put an attachment reply to an email and it's a circus. For me anyway. But the printer works great. It's not color and a little pricy just being a laser b/w laser. I've bought two. I hope they fix/patch a update on the software or send instructions instead of being sent to trouble shoot on their support looking for the specific problem to either understand it or repair a problem. I just cannot search help trouble shoot while working just to bc attach a document after scanning, copying, etc etc.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 24, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Setup was easy. Would like a little more manual in package instead of online. All functions worked first time.

reviews.reviewText: it works flawlessly with Chrome OS and works with all features.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far so good.
reviews.reviewText: Prints and copies well, easy to read and nice and dark. Tech support, phone, helped with a problem, which was my fault. Scanner worked and easy to use.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars So far works well but was impossible to set up.
reviews.reviewText: I am not sure why they make it SO complicated to scan to email. I had to call the geek squad, who was at my house for almost an hour and a half, trying to figure it out. It was something super silly that was not clicked, but I had to set up authentication, special passwords, all kinds of stuff that I did before the geek squad even came. I would recommend if you have your own IT guy/team. But if you’re not tech savvy and setting this up in hopes to use the scan to email feature I’d look elsewhere. I had to pay half the price of the printer for the geek squad to come set it up!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value & easy setup
reviews.reviewText: The printer is awesome!! Much better than HP and was simple to set up and start printing. Printing is quick and good quality. I love the fact that it holds a lot of paper...which is a BIG PLUS!!! Being wireless is also great as I can print directly from my smartphone.
